{"itemid":1248,"subject":"RIP Roger Ebert","event":"I was very saddened today to hear of the death of Roger Ebert.\r\n\r\nRoger (somehow I think of him as 'Roger,' not 'Ebert,' though I never met him in the flesh, and spoke to him only once, by telephone, in the early 1970s when both of us were young and dinosaurs roamed the earth) has been my favorite film critic since forever.  I did not always agree with him, but I always found him insightful and fun to read.  He was not just a terrific critic, he was a terrific WRITER.  His shows with Gene Siskel, SNEAK PREVIEWS and SISKEL AND EBERT AT THE MOVIES, were must-see TV for me.  A hundred other teams have tried to recapture their magic, but none came close.\r\n\r\nHe was One of Us too.  A fan, and an SF fan at that.  In his youth, he wrote for fanzines, and he even published a few short SF stories in Ted White's AMAZING and FANTASTIC along about the same time I was publishing in those selfsame magazines.  If he had not gone on to be the world's best film critic, he might well have been a successful SF writer.\r\n\r\nA brilliant man, a good life.  I give him two thumbs up.","ditemid":319625,"eventtime":"2013-04-05 13:15:00","props":{"current_location":"Santa Fe","taglist":"life and death, movies","current_moodid":25,"commentalter":1366155102,"opt_lockcomments":1,"picture_keyword":"sadface","opt_screening":"F","spam_counter":4,"personifi_tags":"nterms:yes","interface":"web","revnum":1,"revtime":1366912734},"can_comment":0,"logtime":"2013-04-05 19:15:08","anum":137,"url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html","event_timestamp":1365167700,"reply_count":24,"comments":[{"collapsed":0,"shown":1,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17538441#t17538441","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17538441#t17538441","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17538441#t17538441","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_1740258","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://profiles.google.com/117676886377879941860","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":17538441,"talkid":68509,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17538441#t17538441","article":"I'm a huge fan of his writing and I loved him as much as I could love someone with whom I've talked through the internet a few times. I would actually get very sentimental because he meeant (and means) so much to me. Film reviewing is for me part of the cinema world so when I think of the beauty of the movies, Roger easily come to my mind among other things. <br />Thanks for sharing the info that he also wrote SF stories. Such a complex personality..such a beautiful man.","upictitle":"ext_1740258: pic#0","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","stime":"4 years ago","poster":"grrm","ctime":"April 5 2013, 19:33:46 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Roger Ebert","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://profiles.google.com/117676886377879941860","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/google-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"ext_1740258","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_1740258","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=62509544&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"ext_1740258","ctime_ts":1365190426,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/117224364/49319521","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17538953#t17538953","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17538953#t17538953","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17538953#t17538953","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_1195379","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://www.facebook.com/ericporter","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":17538953,"talkid":68511,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17538953#t17538953","upictitle":"Eric Porter: pic#117224364","article":"I was lucky enough to grow up in Chicago being able to watch and read both Siskel and Ebert on a weekly basis. They were a huge catalyst in my love for movies and introduced me to many genre's I would have never found on my own. They are both truly missed.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"4 years ago","ctime":"April 5 2013, 20:05:15 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://www.facebook.com/ericporter","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Eric Porter","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_1195379","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=49319521&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Eric Porter","ctime_ts":1365192315,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/119750848/57819134","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17539209#t17539209","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17539209#t17539209","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17539209#t17539209","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_1579183","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://profiles.google.com/104663581513727253981","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":17539209,"talkid":68512,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17539209#t17539209","upictitle":"Shane Archer: pic#119750848","article":"Can't agree more, Roger Ebert was one of the most readable film critics anywhere, even if you had no real interest in whatever was being reviewed. He always came off as genuinely nice and managed to be critical without being overly negative.<br /><br />When I was younger I'd catch him in the papers or on TV, and now he was always the first Top Critic I'd seek out on rottentomatoes.com or elsewhere. <br /><br />Cheers to Roger for a life well lived!","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"4 years ago","ctime":"April 5 2013, 20:20:59 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://profiles.google.com/104663581513727253981","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/google-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Shane Archer","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_1579183","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=57819134&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Shane Archer","ctime_ts":1365193259,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/120221206/60820474","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17540489#t17540489","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17540489#t17540489","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17540489#t17540489","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_1668887","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://www.facebook.com/bryancogman","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":17540489,"talkid":68517,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17540489#t17540489","upictitle":"Bryan Cogman: pic#120221206","article":"This makes me very very sad. In fact, I haven't been this sad about a celebrity's death since Jim Henson. As a budding film nut, I devoured his 'home video companion', watched his TV show religiously, visited his website weekly, treasured his \"Great Movies\" books... He exposed me at a young age to dozens of films, directors, and writers that I never would have been aware of otherwise. <br /><br />Many years ago, I saw (and hated) MULHOLLAND DRIVE. Ebert gave it a four star review. I wrote him a comment on his 'movie answer man' message board to tell him why I hated it. To my surprise and delight, he emailed me back PERSONALLY to tell me why I was wrong! (I was right, by the way).<br /><br />Guess I'll have to get used to a world where Roger Ebert isn't around to review the latest theatrical release or recommend a classic I haven't seen yet. Feel like I lost a friend.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"4 years ago","ctime":"April 6 2013, 00:21:44 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://www.facebook.com/bryancogman","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Bryan Cogman","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_1668887","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=60820474&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Bryan Cogman","ctime_ts":1365207704,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/119977496/60056006","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17541001#t17541001","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17541001#t17541001","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17541001#t17541001","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_1623298","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://www.facebook.com/ssundram1","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":17541001,"talkid":68519,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17541001#t17541001","upictitle":"Shiv Sundram: pic#119977496","article":"Mr Ebert,<br /><br />If a picture speaks a thousand words, then a two hour film speaks 172,800,000. Few people have the ability to reduce such monstrosity into an elegant one page summary…even fewer have the gift to transmute the beauty of modern cinema into the written word. With that said, the world has just lost a treasure of the written, spoken, and visual arts.<br /><br />Today, Roger Ebert passed away at the age of 70 after battling cancer since 2002. He was a film critic, known most famously as one of the hosts of “At the Movies with Siskel and Ebert.” Together, they popularized the term “two thumbs up,” and for the layman, that may be the only discernible feature of his legacy. But he was more than that…he always manged to remind us of why we loved movies in the first place. His discussions and writings were colloquial enough to be accessible, and yet eloquent enough to be considered art. I would read his reviews avidly, and even when we completely disagreed on a film’s quality, his words were still thoughtful enough to earn my respect. <br /><br />And in 2002 he was diagnosed with a cancer that eventually robbed him of his face and voice. Nevertheless, he continued to watch, write, and review movies until he was recently hospitalized. And most importantly, he never lost his perspective and zest for life. On his impending death, he said <br /><br />“I know it is coming, and I do not fear it, because I believe there is nothing on the other side of death to fear. I hope to be spared as much pain as possible on the approach path. I was perfectly content before I was born, and I think of death as the same state. What I am grateful for is the gift of intelligence, and for life, love, wonder, and laughter.<br /><br />Mr Ebert, your writing was visceral, your passion was tenacious, and above all, your courage was inspiring. My favorite review of all time is yours on Citizen Kane. It begins with:<br /><br />“`I don't think any word can explain a man's life,'' says one of the searchers through the warehouse of treasures left behind by Charles Foster Kane. Then we get the famous series of shots leading to the closeup of the word ``Rosebud''”. <br /><br />To me, Rosebud represents more than just Kane’s longing for the innocence of childhood…it is a symbol of the difficulty of reducing something larger than life into mere words. Every day, Roger Ebert would take on this task with humility, honesty, and his classic touch of humor, whether he was writing about films, society, or his own fight with cancer. And now here I sit, at my own keyboard, unable to do for Roger Ebert what he did so effortlessly for the rest of the world. How does one describe a man like him? It would be fruitless to say that I, or anybody, could do so successfully. So Mr. Ebert. I leave you with one last word:<br /><br />ROSEBUD<br /><br />Rest in peace,<br /><br />One of your biggest fans, <br />Shiv Sundram ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"4 years ago","ctime":"April 6 2013, 01:19:22 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"An incredible, prolific man","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://www.facebook.com/ssundram1","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Shiv Sundram","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_1623298","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=60056006&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Shiv Sundram","ctime_ts":1365211162,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17541769#t17541769","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17541769#t17541769","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17541769#t17541769","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_1740573","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://profiles.google.com/102235239027842202682","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":17541769,"talkid":68522,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17541769#t17541769","upictitle":"ext_1740573: pic#0","article":"We'll never get to hear his review of The Tales of Dunk and Egg movie released in 2018.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"4 years ago","ctime":"April 6 2013, 02:09:12 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Sad day indeed","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://profiles.google.com/102235239027842202682","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/google-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"ext_1740573","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_1740573","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=62522350&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"ext_1740573","ctime_ts":1365214152,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/113603613/4454418","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17544585#t17544585","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17544585#t17544585","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17544585#t17544585","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"gilda_elise","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://gilda-elise.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":17544585,"talkid":68533,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17544585#t17544585","upictitle":"Gilda Elise: Misc-Over the Edge","article":"<i>He was One of Us too. A fan, and an SF fan at that. In his youth, he wrote for fanzines, and he even published a few short SF stories in Ted White's AMAZING and FANTASTIC along about the same time I was publishing in those selfsame magazines. If he had not gone on to be the world's best film critic, he might well have been a successful SF writer.</i><br /><br />I didn't know that about him. Suddenly, his passing is so much more personal. I always enjoyed his show, though. He'll be missed.<br />","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"4 years ago","ctime":"April 6 2013, 09:59:30 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://gilda-elise.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"gilda_elise","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"gilda_elise","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://gilda-elise.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"gilda_elise","ctime_ts":1365242370,"tracked":0},{"shown":0,"collapsed":1,"uname":"the_terrible","loaded":0,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://the-terrible.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":17547401,"talkid":68544,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/319625.html?thread=17547401#t17547401","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"4 years ago","massactions":0,"deleted":1,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://the-terrible.livejournal.com/","striked":1,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","colo